Iavan Pijoos, News24(Supplied to News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Twenty children at a primary school in The Hills, south of Johannesburg, were rushed to hospital with suspected food poisoning on Wednesday morning, paramedics said.They were complaining of abdominal pain and nausea and were vomiting, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said.The children told paramedics they ate sweets an unknown man gave them on Tuesday. They were taken to the South Rand and Chris Hani Baragwanath hospitals.Meiring urged parents to teach their children not to accept sweets or gifts from strangers.Captain Kay Makhubele said no arrest had been made.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.